<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[794,1418,1530,2131]" lastBlockId="4.[170,794,218,627]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,927,1530,1555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Discussion:</emphasis>
This species was described based on a single male specimen from Central Amazon. This is the first mention of a female specimen. The examined specimen corresponds to 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1144,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Helobata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonensis">
<emphasis box="[973,1144,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. amazonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the moderate-size – 5.00 mm in length compared to 
<quantity box="[1144,1239,1658,1683]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.70 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[1311,1414,1658,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">holotype</typeStatus>
; the coloration – dorsum yellow with conspicuous brown areas,pronotum with well-defined central brown area,elytra with faint light brown spots close to humeral humps and diffusely spread throughout elytral disc (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1357,1786,1811]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), and abdominal ventrites yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1166,1818,1843]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); the general morphology of head and mouth parts – anterior clypeal margin convex, slightly truncate medially (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1315,1882,1907]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs. 7-8</figureCitation>
); frontoclypeal suture distinct (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1135,1914,1939]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); maxillary palpomere 3 and 4 subequal in length (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1152,1946,1971]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); mentum without conspicuous microsculpture; the general dorsal sculpture – punctures on elytral rows fine, regularly spaced (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1407,2010,2035]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); the presence of fine and very short decumbent setae distributed on anterior half of the clypeus; the general morphology of the ventral projections – posteromedial elevation on mesoventrite semi-trapezoidal, very wide, with strongly raised lateral carinae, oblique, widely distant each other, converging anteriorly; widely connected with the metaventral projection (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1291,218,243]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); metaventral projection (between mesocoxae) forming an elevated longitudinal carina, strongly and widely connected posteriorly with metaventral medial carina; metaventral medial carina rising gradually until connecting to metaventral projection (
<figureCitation box="[297,358,282,307]" captionStart="Figures 7-11" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[119,1392,210,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[113,1398,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 7-11. (7-8) Helobata amazonensis Clarkson,Santos &amp; Ferreira-Jr. Habitus, (7) dorsal view, (8) ventral view, scale = 2.0 mm; (9-11) Helobata sp. Habitus, (9) dorsal view,(10) ventral view,scale = 2.0 mm;abdominal ventrites,(11) ventral view,scale = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
